<%# locals: (form:, field_name:) -%>
<div data-controller="codemirror">
  <%= form.label field_name, "Script body", class: "block text-sm font-medium text-text-muted mb-1" %>
  <%= form.text_area field_name, rows: 20,
    data: { codemirror_target: "textarea" },
    placeholder: "# Your Ruby script runs when this fires.\n# Return a string to send a reply.",
    class: "w-full rounded-md border border-border bg-surface px-3 py-2 text-sm font-mono text-text placeholder:text-text-faint focus:border-primary focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-primary" %>
  <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-text-faint">Ruby script. Return a string to reply, or call <code class="text-primary">send_message(text)</code> for multi-message flows.</p>
</div>

<details open class="mt-3 rounded-md border border-border bg-surface-raised">
  <summary class="cursor-pointer px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-text-muted select-none">Scripting Reference</summary>
  <div class="px-4 pb-4 pt-2 space-y-3 text-xs">
    <div>
      <h4 class="font-medium text-text mb-1">Variables</h4>
      <table class="w-full">
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-border text-text-muted">
          <tr><td class="py-1 pr-3 font-mono text-primary">message</td><td class="py-1">Full message text (nil for scheduled actions)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1 pr-3 font-mono text-primary">author</td><td class="py-1">Sender's identifier (nil for scheduled actions)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1 pr-3 font-mono text-primary">args</td><td class="py-1">Extracted arguments after the command pattern (commands only)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1 pr-3 font-mono text-primary">bot_name</td><td class="py-1">The bot's display name</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1 pr-3 font-mono text-primary">group_id</td><td class="py-1">The MLS group ID</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h4 class="font-medium text-text mb-1">Methods</h4>
      <table class="w-full">
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-border text-text-muted">
          <tr><td class="py-1 pr-3 font-mono text-primary">send_message(text)</td><td class="py-1">Send a message to the group (can call multiple times)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1 pr-3 font-mono text-primary">store[key]</td><td class="py-1">Read from persistent per-bot key-value store</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1 pr-3 font-mono text-primary">store[key] = val</td><td class="py-1">Write to store (saved after script completes)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1 pr-3 font-mono text-primary">http_get(url)</td><td class="py-1">GET request, auto-parses JSON (options: headers:, timeout:)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1 pr-3 font-mono text-primary">http_post(url)</td><td class="py-1">POST request (options: body:, headers:, timeout:)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h4 class="font-medium text-text mb-1">Network (wnd)</h4>
      <table class="w-full">
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-border text-text-muted">
          <tr><td class="py-1 pr-3 font-mono text-primary">wnd.user(pubkey)</td><td class="py-1">Look up a user's profile by public key</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1 pr-3 font-mono text-primary">wnd.members(group_id)</td><td class="py-1">List members of a group</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1 pr-3 font-mono text-primary">wnd.profile</td><td class="py-1">The bot's own profile</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1 pr-3 font-mono text-primary">wnd.groups</td><td class="py-1">List groups the bot is in</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1 pr-3 font-mono text-primary">wnd.invites</td><td class="py-1">List pending group invitations</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1 pr-3 font-mono text-primary">wnd.accept_invite(group_id)</td><td class="py-1">Accept a group invitation</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-1 pr-3 font-mono text-primary">wnd.decline_invite(group_id)</td><td class="py-1">Decline a group invitation</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h4 class="font-medium text-text mb-1">Tips</h4>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-4 text-text-muted space-y-0.5">
        <li>Return a string to send one final reply. Return <code class="text-primary">nil</code> to stay silent.</li>
        <li>All scripts on this bot share the same <code class="text-primary">store</code>. Use descriptive keys to avoid collisions.</li>
        <li>Use <code class="text-primary">group_id</code> to namespace per-group state: <code class="text-primary">store["mykey_#{group_id}"]</code></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h4 class="font-medium text-text mb-1">Examples</h4>
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <div>
          <p class="text-text-muted mb-1">Weather lookup:</p>
          <pre class="rounded bg-surface px-3 py-2 font-mono text-text overflow-x-auto" data-controller="codemirror-readonly">city = args.presence || "New York"
data = http_get("https://wttr.in/#{URI.encode_www_form_component(city)}?format=3")
data.is_a?(String) ? data : "Weather data unavailable"</pre>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="text-text-muted mb-1">Remember and recall:</p>
          <pre class="rounded bg-surface px-3 py-2 font-mono text-text overflow-x-auto" data-controller="codemirror-readonly">if args.present?
  store["remember_notes"] ||= []
  store["remember_notes"] << args
  "Remembered. #{store['remember_notes'].size} note(s) stored."
else
  notes = store["remember_notes"] || []
  notes.empty? ? "Nothing stored." : notes.join("\n")
end</pre>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="text-text-muted mb-1">Coin flip:</p>
          <pre class="rounded bg-surface px-3 py-2 font-mono text-text overflow-x-auto" data-controller="codemirror-readonly">%w[Heads Tails].sample</pre>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="text-text-muted mb-1">Counter:</p>
          <pre class="rounded bg-surface px-3 py-2 font-mono text-text overflow-x-auto" data-controller="codemirror-readonly">store["counter_total"] = (store["counter_total"] || 0) + 1
"This command has been used #{store['counter_total']} time(s)."</pre>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="text-text-muted mb-1">Per-group counter:</p>
          <pre class="rounded bg-surface px-3 py-2 font-mono text-text overflow-x-auto" data-controller="codemirror-readonly">key = "counter_#{group_id}"
store[key] = (store[key] || 0) + 1
"This group's count: #{store[key]}"</pre>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="text-text-muted mb-1">Daily greeting (scheduled action):</p>
          <pre class="rounded bg-surface px-3 py-2 font-mono text-text overflow-x-auto" data-controller="codemirror-readonly">greetings = ["Good morning!", "Rise and shine!", "Hello, world!"]
greetings.sample</pre>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="text-text-muted mb-1">Who said that:</p>
          <pre class="rounded bg-surface px-3 py-2 font-mono text-text overflow-x-auto" data-controller="codemirror-readonly">profile = wnd.user(author)
meta = profile&.dig("metadata") || {}
name = meta["display_name"].presence || meta["name"].presence || "unknown"
"That was #{name}"</pre>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="text-text-muted mb-1">Multi-message lookup:</p>
          <pre class="rounded bg-surface px-3 py-2 font-mono text-text overflow-x-auto" data-controller="codemirror-readonly">send_message("Looking up #{args}...")
data = http_get("https://api.example.com/search?q=#{URI.encode_www_form_component(args)}")
results = data["items"] || []
if results.empty?
  "No results found."
else
  results.first(3).each { |item| send_message("- #{item['name']}: #{item['url']}") }
  nil  # no extra final message
end</pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</details>
